  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer C&S",
  "description": "<p>Responsibility</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To supervise the construction works in accordance to the project specifications, construction drawings, and Building Control Acts and Regulations</li>\n  <li>To inspect the works to ensure that work is carried out in accordance to the Qualified Person (QP)      instruction</li>\n  <li>To keep proper site inspection records and accurate records of site progress</li>\n  <li>Check drawings and specifications for discrepancies and highlight to QP and Contractor, suggesting possible solutions to prevent delays</li>\n  <li>Review contractor’s method statements, highlight discrepancies and inspect works on site to ensure contractor execute works in accordance to approved method statement</li>\n  <li>Enforce quality control on site and monitor site safety</li>\n  <li>Attend site meeting and coordinate with QP and Contractor with site inspections</li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit daily site activities report, and monthly progress report</li>\n  <li>Present during all critical structural works such as concreting, fixing of reinforcement, installation      and removal of temporary support</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirement</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Civil Engineering, National Construction Certificate of Supervision (NCCS) or diploma</li>\n  <li>Registered with IES/ACES as Resident Technical Officer</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years relevant site experience in residential / improvement works.</li>\n  <li>Experience in HDB's works, LTA projects is a strong advantage</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
